According to the annotation (`import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test`), you are trying to run JUnit 5 tests with Maven. According to the [documentation][1], you have to add this dependency:

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter-engine&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;5.3.1&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

Your version of Maven comes with a version of `maven-surefire-plugin` which does not support JUnit 5. You could update your Maven to the latest version. You could also set the version of the `maven-surefire-plugin`:

    &lt;plugin&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;!-- JUnit 5 requires Surefire version 2.22.0 or higher --&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;2.22.0&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;/plugin&gt;

See the [junit5-samples for this information][2].

See the [Maven Surefire Plugin][3] artifact in a Maven repository. At version `3.0.0-M3` as of 2019-01.


  [1]: https://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/examples/junit-platform.html
  [2]: https://github.com/junit-team/junit5-samples/blob/r5.3.1/junit5-jupiter-starter-maven/pom.xml
  [3]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.apache.maven.plugins/maven-surefire-plugin

# tl;dr

Add two dependencies to your project:

 - *JUnit Jupiter (Aggregator)*
 - *Maven Surefire Plugin*

```xml
&lt;!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.junit.jupiter/junit-jupiter --&gt;
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;5.9.1&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

… and:

```xml
&lt;!-- https://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/dependency-info.html --&gt;
&lt;dependency&gt;
  &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
  &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
  &lt;version&gt;3.0.0-M7&lt;/version&gt;
  &lt;type&gt;maven-plugin&lt;/type&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```



# `junit-jupiter` —&#160;the simpler archetype for JUnit 5

The [Answer by LaurentG][1] seems to be correct, but a bit outdated.

As of JUnit 5.4, you can **replace those multiple Maven artifacts**:

 - `junit`
 - `junit-jupiter-api`
 - `junit-jupiter-engine`

…with a single artifact:

 - [`junit-jupiter`][2]

…to run JUnit 5 tests.

This artifact is an aggregate of other artifacts, a convenient wrapper to simplify your POM file. See [this repository](https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.junit.jupiter/junit-jupiter). 

```xml
&lt;!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.junit.jupiter/junit-jupiter --&gt;
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;5.9.1&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

This gives you all you need to write and run JUnit 5 *Jupiter* tests.

# `maven-surefire-plugin`

You would also need the [*Surefire* plugin][5] as shown in that [other Answer][1]. Be sure to get the latest version, as Surefire has had some important fixes/enhancements recently. 

See [this list][6] of dependency declarations for Maven, Buildr, Ivy, Grape, Grails, SBT, and Leiningen. To quote the Maven config:

```xml
&lt;!-- https://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/dependency-info.html --&gt;
&lt;dependency&gt;
  &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
  &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
  &lt;version&gt;3.0.0-M7&lt;/version&gt;
  &lt;type&gt;maven-plugin&lt;/type&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```



# `junit-vintage-engine` for JUnit 3 &amp; 4 tests 

If you have old JUnit 3 or JUnit 4 [legacy][3] tests that you want to continue to run, add another dependency, [`junit-vintage-engine`][4]. 

```xml
&lt;!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.junit.vintage/junit-vintage-engine --&gt;
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.vintage&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-vintage-engine&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;5.9.1&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```



  [1]: https://stackoverflow.com/a/53433724/642706
  [2]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.junit.jupiter/junit-jupiter
  [3]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legacy_system
  [4]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.junit.vintage/junit-vintage-engine
  [5]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.apache.maven.plugins/maven-surefire-plugin
  [6]: https://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/dependency-info.html

Add &quot;include&quot; in configuration section for maven surfire, your test should end with Test.java and it should work


